    <h2>Message queue plugin</h2>
    <hr/>
    <p>
        <strong>MqPlugin</strong> enables to set up and verify the state of a some message queue. Message queue is represented as
        an implementation of the <code>io.github.adven27.concordion.extensions.exam.mq.MqTester</code> interface
        and basically <strong>off loads all the responsibilities for working with the specific queue to that implementation</strong>.
    </p>
    <p>
       There are several out-of-teb-box implementations
        (<a href="https://github.com/Adven27/Exam/tree/master/exam-mq-kafka">exam-mq-kafka</a> /
        <a href="https://github.com/Adven27/Exam/tree/master/exam-mq-rabbit">exam-mq-rabbit</a> /
        <a href="https://github.com/Adven27/Exam/tree/master/exam-mq-ibmmq">exam-mq-ibmmq</a> /
        <a href="https://github.com/Adven27/Exam/tree/master/exam-mq-redis">exam-mq-redis</a>)
        that can be used directly or as an example for custom ones.
    </p>

    <h3>Usage</h3>
    <p>1. Add dependency <pre class="doc-code"><code>testImplementation "io.github.adven27:exam-mq:5.0.1"</code></pre></p>
    <p>2. Configure and attach to ExamExtension the <a cc:run="concordion" href="mq/MqPlugin.html">MqPlugin</a></p>

    <h3>Commands</h3>
    <p>
        There are commands for setting up and verifying queue state.
    </p>

    <h4>Set up queue</h4>

    <dl>
        <dt><code><a cc:run="concordion" href="mq/MqSend.html">mq-send</a></code></dt>
        <dd>
            <p>Sends message to specified queue</p>
            <pre class="doc-code language-xml"><code> <![CDATA[<e:mq-send name="someQueue" from="/data/message.json"/>]]> </code></pre>
        </dd>
        <dt><code><a cc:run="concordion" href="mq/MqPurge.html">mq-purge</a></code></dt>
        <dd>
            <p>Purges specified queue</p>
            <pre class="doc-code language-xml"><code><![CDATA[<e:mq-purge name="someQueue"/>]]></code></pre>
        </dd>
    </dl>

    <h4>Verify queue</h4>

    <dl>
        <dt><code><a cc:run="concordion" href="mq/MqCheck.html">mq-check</a></code></dt>
        <dd>
            <p>Verifies that specified messages exist in queue</p>
            <pre class="doc-code language-xml"><code><![CDATA[<e:mq-check name="someQueue">
    <e:message>{"msg" : "1"}</e:message>
    <e:message from="/data/mq/msg2.json"/>
</e:mq-check>]]></code></pre>
        </dd>
    </dl>

